Privacy Policy for Car Spotters Mobile App
Effective Date:
December 20, 2024.
Car Spotters ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use the Car Spotters mobile app ("App"). Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your information.
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Information You Provide
Account Information:
When you register, we collect your name, email address, username, and any additional details you choose to provide.
User Content:
Photos, comments, and other content you upload to the App.
Communications:
Information you provide when contacting our support team or other users through the App.
1.2 Information Collected Automatically
Location Data:
Your precise or approximate location is collected to display nearby car spots and enhance the user experience.
Device Information:
Includes device type, operating system, unique device identifiers, and network information.
Usage Data:
Data on your interaction with the App, such as features used, pages viewed, and time spent on the App.
1.3 Information from Third Parties
We may receive information from third-party services if you choose to connect them to your Car Spotters account.
2. How We Use Your Information
To provide, operate, and maintain the App and its features.
To personalize your experience by displaying relevant car spots and other content.
To communicate with you, including sending updates, notifications, and promotional content (if consented to).
To monitor and analyze App usage and performance for improvement.
To ensure compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and policies.
3. Sharing Your Information
3.1 With Other Users
Content you post, such as photos or comments, may be visible to other users.
3.2 With Service Providers
We may share your data with third-party vendors that assist in operations, such as hosting services, analytics, or customer support.
3.3 For Legal Reasons
We may disclose your information to comply with legal obligations, protect our rights, or respond to lawful requests.
3.4 In Business Transfers
If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
4. Your Rights and Choices
4.1 Managing Your Information
You can update or delete your account information in the App settings or by contacting us at
support@carspot.live
.
4.2 Location Data
You can disable location tracking in your device settings. Note that some features may not function without location data.
4.3 Marketing Communications
You can opt out of receiving promotional communications by following the unsubscribe instructions in the emails.
5. Data Security
We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your information. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.
6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Car Spotters is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected such information, please contact us, and we will promptly delete it.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be posted in the App, and the "Effective Date" at the top will be updated. Continued use of the App after changes indicates acceptance of the revised policy.
8. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:
Car Spotters Support Team
Email:
support@carspot.live